00:00:45.590 --> 00:00:49.190
So one little tip which you may find useful is

00:00:49.190 --> 00:00:53.285
before actually drawing the curves for a lot of the face,

00:00:53.285 --> 00:00:58.930
you may find it a lot easy by creating some small arcs as reference points.

00:00:58.930 --> 00:01:03.185
For example, the start and the ending point of a curve,

00:01:03.185 --> 00:01:06.920
and this is what I do when creating this example and having

00:01:06.920 --> 00:01:11.890
these reference points to hand really does make it a lot easier when drawing the curves.

00:01:11.890 --> 00:01:16.550
So go ahead and spend a little time trying to replicate this,

00:01:16.550 --> 00:01:19.715
